headline: International Paper (IP): Losses Worsen by 10.5% Annually, Profitability Hinges on Forecasted Turnaround
summary: International Paper (IP) is currently unprofitable, with net losses worsening at an average rate of 10.5% per year over the last five years. Looking ahead, analysts forecast earnings to grow by 19.92% annually, and expect the company to swing to profitability within three years, a turnaround that stands well above the broader market’s average pace. Despite muted revenue growth expectations of 2.7% per year, the stock, at $38.63, trades not only below the industry average Price-to-Sales...
